Record Class Booking

booking.Booking
Record Components:

public record Booking(UUID processID, List<BookingRequest> requests) extends Record
Represents a booking with a unique process ID and a list of booking requests. This class is a record, providing a compact syntax for declaring data carrier classes.

  • Constructor Details

    • Booking

      public Booking(UUID processID, List<BookingRequest> requests)
      Constructs a new Booking with the specified process ID and list of BookingRequest. The list of booking requests is wrapped in a CopyOnWriteArrayList to ensure thread safety.
      Parameters:
      processID - the unique identifier for this booking process.
      requests - the list of BookingRequest associated with this booking.

  • Method Details

    • isCancelling

      public boolean isCancelling()
      Checks if the booking is in the process of being cancelled. A booking is considered to be cancelling if any of its requests are rejected or have exceeded their retry limit.
      Returns:
      true if any booking request is rejected or retries exceeded, false otherwise.

    • isSuccessful

      public boolean isSuccessful()
      Checks if the booking is successful. A booking is considered successful if none of its BookingRequest are BookingRequest.isFailed(),BookingRequest.isRejected(), or BookingRequest.isCancelled().
      Returns:
      true if all BookingRequest are successful, false if at least 1 BookingRequest fails, is rejected, or is cancelled.

    • uncompletedRequests

      public List<BookingRequest> uncompletedRequests()
      Retrieves a list of uncompleted booking requests. A booking request is considered uncompleted if BookingRequest.isCompleted() returns false.
      Returns:
      a list of uncompleted BookingRequest.
